ZH: 他今天就任了新的职位。
EN: He took office in his new position today.

ZH: 她在上个月就任了公司的首席执行官。
EN: She assumed the role of CEO in the company last month.

ZH: 明年，这位年轻的政治家将就任总统。
EN: Next year, this young politician will assume the presidency.

ZH: 这位教授已经就任教育部副部长。
EN: The professor has already taken up the position of Deputy Minister of Education.

ZH: 他在国际组织中就任了一项重要职务。
EN: He has assumed an important role in an international organization.

ZH: 昨天，新的校长就任了学校的领导职位。
EN: Yesterday, the new principal assumed the leadership position in the school.

ZH: 总统将于下周就任第二个任期。
EN: The president will take office for a second term next week.

ZH: 他在年初就任新的经理职位。
EN: He assumed a new managerial position at the beginning of the year.

ZH: 他将很快就任军队的最高指挥官。
EN: He will soon assume the role of the highest military commander.

ZH: 众议院议长将于明天就任。
EN: The Speaker of the House will take office tomorrow.

ZH: 她在多个国家的大使馆就任了外交官职务。
EN: She assumed diplomatic positions at several embassies in different countries.

ZH: 这位年轻的企业家将就任公司的董事长一职。
EN: This young entrepreneur will assume the position of chairman of the company.

ZH: 在过去十年中，他就任了许多重要职务。
EN: Over the past decade, he has assumed many significant positions.

ZH: 他在政府机构中就任了一项关键职位。
EN: He assumed a critical position in a government agency.

ZH: 国际组织将就任新的秘书长。
EN: The international organization will appoint a new secretary-general.

ZH: 今年，她将就任大学的系主任。
EN: This year, she will assume the position of department head at the university.

ZH: 公司决定给他就任一项重要项目的责任。
EN: The company has decided to assign him the responsibility of heading an important project.

ZH: 我希望你能成功就任这份工作。
EN: I hope you succeed in taking up this job.

ZH: 这位新的市长将在明天就任。
EN: The new mayor will take office tomorrow.

ZH: 几周后，他将就任新的法官职位。
EN: After a few weeks, he will assume a new position as a judge.

ZH: 他将成为第一位就任这个职务的女性。
EN: She will become the first woman to take up this position.
